The paper discusses adaptive networks and their ability to perform decentralized information processing and optimization tasks, which are topics typically covered in the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses optimization and estimation problems, which are topics covered in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of diffusion strategies for adaptation and learning is a topic covered in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses network conditions and information exchanges, which are topics covered in the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses performance comparisons of different strategies, which is a topic covered in the sub-category of cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
